{"config":{"lang":["en"],"separator":"[\\s\\-]+","pipeline":["stopWordFilter"],"fields":{"title":{"boost":1000.0},"text":{"boost":1.0},"tags":{"boost":1000000.0}}},"docs":[{"location":"","title":"Welcome to the MeTTa Resource Portal","text":"<p>This portal is a comprehensive collection of resources, curriculum, and projects for the MeTTa programming language.</p> <p> Comprehensive Curriculum</p> <p>From functional foundations to advanced Neurosymbolic AI architectures using MeTTa and Hyperon.</p> <p> Self-Paced Learning</p> <p>Explore at your own speed, from foundational concepts to advanced cognitive architectures.</p> <p> Community Driven</p> <p>Open access materials for anyone interested in MeTTa development.</p> <p> Practical Implementation</p> <p>Learn how to build functional projects using MORK and Atomspace.</p>"},{"location":"#overview","title":"Overview","text":"<p>MeTTa is a unique programming language designed for cognitive computing and neurosymbolic AI. This site provides a structured path for learning the language, along with a library of resources and examples.</p>"},{"location":"#curriculum","title":"Curriculum","text":"<p>The curriculum is structured into modules, taking you from basic functional programming to complex cognitive architectures.</p>"},{"location":"#resources","title":"Resources","text":"<p>Check our Resources section for links to setup guides, documentation, and video tutorials.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/","title":"Curriculum","text":"<p>This curriculum outlines a structured path for learning MeTTa. Lessons are numbered sequentially to guide you through the language's concepts.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#module-1-foundations-of-metta","title":"Module 1: Foundations of MeTTa","text":"<p>Focus: Syntax, Functional Programming, and Data Types.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-01-introduction","title":"Lesson 01: Introduction","text":"<ul> <li>Resource allocation and setup guide.</li> <li>Workflow overview.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-02-functional-js-foundations","title":"Lesson 02: Functional JS Foundations","text":"<ul> <li>Functional programming paradigms.</li> <li>Recursion and Immutability.</li> <li>Higher-order functions.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-03-metta-basics-part-i","title":"Lesson 03: MeTTa Basics (Part I)","text":"<ul> <li>Environment setup.</li> <li>Basic syntax structure.</li> <li>Built-in data types.</li> <li>Variables and function definitions.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-04-metta-basics-part-ii","title":"Lesson 04: MeTTa Basics (Part II)","text":"<ul> <li>Control flow and loops.</li> <li>Iterating over expressions.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-05-atomspace-fundamentals","title":"Lesson 05: Atomspace Fundamentals","text":"<ul> <li>Introduction to Atomspace concepts.</li> <li>Pattern matching logic.</li> <li>Revisiting functions/bindings with pattern matching.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-06-standard-library","title":"Lesson 06: Standard Library","text":"<ul> <li>Utilizing standard libraries for complex logic.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#module-2-advanced-logic-data-structures","title":"Module 2: Advanced Logic &amp; Data Structures","text":"<p>Focus: Files, Recursion, and Type Systems.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-07-files-and-modules","title":"Lesson 07: Files and Modules","text":"<ul> <li>Module management.</li> <li>File manipulation.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-08-recursive-logic","title":"Lesson 08: Recursive Logic","text":"<ul> <li>Converting iterative logic to recursive structures.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-09-higher-order-logic","title":"Lesson 09: Higher Order Logic","text":"<ul> <li>Advanced higher-order functions.</li> <li>Refactoring recursive logic.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-10-data-structures","title":"Lesson 10: Data Structures","text":"<ul> <li>Types and constructors.</li> <li>Lists, Trees, Sets, and Maps.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-11-state-bindings","title":"Lesson 11: State &amp; Bindings","text":"<ul> <li>State Monad.</li> <li>Python bindings and mutable structures.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#module-3-building-non-determinism","title":"Module 3: Building &amp; Non-Determinism","text":"<p>Focus: Application and Space Operations.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-12-revision","title":"Lesson 12: Revision","text":"<ul> <li>Practical review of concepts covered to date.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-13-live-build","title":"Lesson 13: Live Build","text":"<ul> <li>Guided coding lesson.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-14-practical-exercise","title":"Lesson 14: Practical Exercise","text":"<ul> <li>Segmented building exercises.</li> <li>Real-time alignment and troubleshooting.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-15-non-determinism","title":"Lesson 15: Non-Determinism","text":"<ul> <li>Introduction to non-deterministic logic.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-16-applied-non-determinism","title":"Lesson 16: Applied Non-Determinism","text":"<ul> <li>Practical exercises.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-17-atomspace-revision","title":"Lesson 17: Atomspace Revision","text":"<ul> <li>Space operations review.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-18-custom-atomspaces","title":"Lesson 18: Custom Atomspaces","text":"<ul> <li>Creating custom and nested spaces.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#module-4-integration-mork","title":"Module 4: Integration &amp; MORK","text":"<p>Focus: Python Integration, Debugging, and the MORK Engine.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-19-use-cases","title":"Lesson 19: Use Cases","text":"<ul> <li>Common Atomspace design patterns.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-20-practical-application","title":"Lesson 20: Practical Application","text":"<ul> <li>Exercise: Atomspace implementation.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-21-unification","title":"Lesson 21: Unification","text":"<ul> <li>Self-rewriting code.</li> <li>Unification examples.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-22-python-integration-i","title":"Lesson 22: Python Integration (I)","text":"<ul> <li>Custom function wrapping.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-23-python-integration-ii","title":"Lesson 23: Python Integration (II)","text":"<ul> <li>Advanced integration patterns.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-24-debugging-i","title":"Lesson 24: Debugging (I)","text":"<ul> <li>Project initiation and design.</li> <li>Debugging techniques.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-25-debugging-ii","title":"Lesson 25: Debugging (II)","text":"<ul> <li>Advanced troubleshooting.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-26-intro-to-mork-i","title":"Lesson 26: Intro to MORK (I)","text":"<ul> <li>Architecture differences.</li> <li>Environment setup.</li> <li>Pattern matching queries.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-27-intro-to-mork-ii","title":"Lesson 27: Intro to MORK (II)","text":"<ul> <li>MM2 architecture.</li> <li>Code stepping.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#module-5-mm2-deep-dive","title":"Module 5: MM2 Deep Dive","text":"<p>Focus: Sources, Sinks, and Control Logic.</p>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-28-mm2-fundamentals","title":"Lesson 28: MM2 Fundamentals","text":"<ul> <li>Sources, Sinks, and Priority.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-29-set-operations-i","title":"Lesson 29: Set Operations (I)","text":"<ul> <li>Basic set logic.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-30-set-operations-ii","title":"Lesson 30: Set Operations (II)","text":"<ul> <li>Advanced set logic.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-31-project-design-review","title":"Lesson 31: Project Design Review","text":"<ul> <li>Idea validation and structured approach.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-32-control-logic-i","title":"Lesson 32: Control Logic (I)","text":"<ul> <li>MM2