n Networks).</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-45-algorithms-iii","title":"Lesson 45: Algorithms (III)","text":"<ul> <li>Pattern Miner.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-46-algorithms-iv","title":"Lesson 46: Algorithms (IV)","text":"<ul> <li>MOSES.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-47-algorithms-v","title":"Lesson 47: Algorithms (V)","text":"<ul> <li>PLN (Probabilistic Logic Networks).</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-48-algorithms-vi","title":"Lesson 48: Algorithms (VI)","text":"<ul> <li>Cognitive Synergy.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-49-ecosystem","title":"Lesson 49: Ecosystem","text":"<ul> <li>Alternative Compilers (PeTTa).</li> <li>ASI Chain and MeTTaIL.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-50-development-mentoring","title":"Lesson 50: Development Mentoring","text":"<ul> <li>Project guidance.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"curriculum/#lesson-51-development-mentoring","title":"Lesson 51: Development Mentoring","text":"<ul> <li>Project guidance.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"projects/","title":"Projects","text":"<p>Practical application is key to mastering MeTTa. This page provides guidance and ideas for projects using MeTTa and the Atomspace.</p>"},{"location":"projects/#project-guidance","title":"Project Guidance","text":"<p>When starting a MeTTa project, consider the following:</p> <ul> <li>Logic and Integration: How will your symbolic logic interact with external data or Python-based tools?</li> <li>Space Management: How will you structure your Atomspaces for efficient pattern matching?</li> <li>Architecture: Utilize the MM2 architecture (Sources, Sinks, Priority) for large-scale applications.</li> </ul>"},{"location":"projects/#project-ideas","title":"Project Ideas","text":"<ol> <li>Expert Systems: Build a diagnostic tool or recommendation engine using symbolic rules.</li> <li>Natural Language Processing: Use pattern matching to parse and analyze text structures.</li> <li>Robotic Control: Implement high-level decision-making logic for autonomous agents.</li> <li>Knowledge Graphs: Create and query complex relational data using custom Atomspaces.</li> </ol>"},{"location":"projects/#evaluation-and-refinement","title":"Evaluation and Refinement","text":"<p>Successful MeTTa projects demonstrate: - Correct usage of MeTTa syntax and built-in types. - Efficient pattern matching and space operations. - Clear separation between logic and implementation.</p>"},{"location":"resources/","title":"Resources","text":"<p>Reference materials to support your learning journey.</p>"},{"location":"resources/#setup-basics","title":"Setup &amp; Basics","text":"<ul> <li>MeTTa Setup Tutorial</li> <li>Official MeTTa Documentation</li> <li>Additional MeTTa Documentation</li> </ul>"},{"location":"resources/#core-concepts","title":"Core Concepts","text":"<ul> <li>Knowledge Representation using MeTTa</li> <li>Working with Spaces</li> <li>Python Integration using MeTTa</li> </ul>"},{"location":"resources/#debugging","title":"Debugging","text":"<ul> <li>Console Output and Debugging MeTTa</li> </ul>"}]}